# Premium Circle Video Player - Real-time Data Integration

The [CircleVideoPlayer](file:///c:/Users/elink/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideoPlayer.tsx#31-480) has been fully integrated with real-time data, removing all mock content and aligning with the MomsNest production standards.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Real-time Interactions System
- **Database Schema**: Created a robust interaction layer with the following tables:
  - `circle_video_likes`: Tracks unique user likes with real-time counting.
  - `circle_video_comments`: Full nested comment system with user profiles.
  - `circle_video_stats`: Atomic tracking for shares and total engagement.
- **Supabase Real-time**: Implemented a dedicated hook [useCircleVideoInteractions](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/hooks/useCircleVideoInteractions.ts#21-209) that uses Supabase's real-time subscriptions to update likes, comments, and shares instantly across all clients.

### 2. Dynamic Circle Context
- **Circle Branding**: The player now displays the live Circle Name and verified badge.
- **Member Awareness**: Shows the real-time member count from the `circle_stats` table.
- **Avatar Integration**: Uses the official Circle avatar with a premium fallback mechanism.

### 3. UI Refinements & User Experience
- **Header Overhaul**: 
  - Moved the **Back Button** and **Close Button** into a dedicated header section **above** the video player (no longer an overlay).
  - This ensures navigation is always accessible and provides a cleaner video viewing area.
  - Styled both icons with the `primary` color for high visibility.
- **Premium Overlay Aesthetics**:
  - Implemented **High-Transparency Glassmorphism** for the control overlays, optimizing for a clearer view while maintaining the frosted glass effect.
  - **Precision Cropped Background**: The glass background for the bottom controls is now precisely cropped to start exactly from the **bottom edge** of the timeline slider, leaving the timeline and time labels "clean" and floating for better visibility.
  - **Dynamic Visibility Sync**: Overlays (Center and Bottom) are now perfectly synced with the video state—they appear instantly when **Paused** and hide completely when **Playing** for a distraction-free experience.
  - Refined the **video timeline** to be significantly thinner (3px track), creating a more professional and less intrusive interface.
- **Collapsible Elements**:
  - **Description**: Truncates long text with a "Read More" button to keep the focus on the video.
  - **Comments**: Shows initial top comments with a "View all" expansion feature.
- **Overlay Polish**:
  - Rewind/Forward icons are now styled with the `primary` color on a clean white background.
  - Removed simulated iPhone headers and corner circular backgrounds for a native app feel.
- **Full-Screen Fit**: The player modal is now explicitly styled to fit `100vw` and `100vh`, ensuring a seamless experience on all screen sizes.

### 5. Background Upload System
- **Global Upload Tracking**: Created a centralized [UploadContext](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/contexts/UploadContext.tsx#14-21) to manage multiple concurrent video uploads across the entire application.
- **Real-time Percentage Feedback**: Integrated Supabase Storage [onUploadProgress](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/hooks/useCircleVideos.ts#113-117) to provide accurate, second-by-second upload percentages.
- **Persistent Overlay**: Implemented a floating [UploadProgressOverlay](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/UploadProgressOverlay.tsx#6-67) that remains visible even after the upload dialog is closed, fulfilling the "background" requirement.
- **Auto-Continuation**: Users can now start an upload and immediately close the window to continue browsing other features while the progress tracks in the bottom-right corner.
- **Success/Error States**: Elegant visual feedback for completed uploads and descriptive error messages for failures.

